---
import ServiceLayout from '../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import ProcessSteps from '../components/ProcessSteps.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const title = "Trim Restoration Fort Lauderdale | Mobile Service | Route95";
const description = "Professional trim restoration in Fort Lauderdale. Restore faded black plastic trim, remove oxidation, long-lasting protection. Mobile service! Call 754-215-2272";

const parentCategory = {
  href: `${base}car-wash-fort-lauderdale/`,
  title: "Car Wash Services"
};
---

<ServiceLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  h1="Trim Restoration Fort Lauderdale"
  intro="Professional trim restoration brings faded, gray plastic trim back to rich black, reversing years of sun damage and oxidation caused by Florida's harsh conditions."
  currentPage="/trim-restoration-fort-lauderdale/"
  parentCategory={parentCategory}
>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
    <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-8">
      <section>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          Nothing ages a car faster than faded plastic trim. Those black moldings around windows, mirrors, bumpers, and fenders turn chalky gray when UV rays break down the plastic. In Fort Lauderdale, this happens faster than almost anywhere else—our intense sun, humidity, and salt air create perfect conditions for trim degradation.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          You've probably tried tire shine or household products that make trim look good for a day before washing off or leaving a greasy mess. These temporary fixes don't address the underlying oxidation and often make the problem worse by attracting dirt.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          We use Chemical Guys VRP and professional trim restoration products that penetrate plastic, restore the dark color from within, and provide UV protection to prevent future fading. Our mobile service brings this transformation directly to your Fort Lauderdale location.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1e3a5f] mb-4">How Much Does Trim Restoration Cost in Fort Lauderdale?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>Professional trim restoration in Fort Lauderdale costs $50 to $100 depending on the amount of trim and condition.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Vehicles with minimal trim and light fading fall at the lower end. SUVs and trucks with extensive body cladding, severely faded pieces, or multiple panels requiring restoration cost more. Extremely damaged trim may need multiple treatments.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1e3a5f] mb-4">How Long Does Trim Restoration Take?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>Trim restoration takes 30 to 60 minutes depending on the amount of trim and severity of fading.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Each trim piece needs to be cleaned, treated, and allowed to absorb the restoration product. Heavily faded trim may need multiple applications. The results are immediate—you'll see the transformation as we work.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1e3a5f] mb-4">Why Trim Restoration Matters in South Florida</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>Fort Lauderdale's UV index regularly exceeds 10—extreme levels that destroy plastic trim in months, not years.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Problems caused by faded trim:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-4 space-y-2">
          <li>Chalky, gray appearance that makes cars look old</li>
          <li>Plastic becomes brittle and prone to cracking</li>
          <li>Uneven fading creates a patchy, neglected look</li>
          <li>Contrast with clean paint makes fading more obvious</li>
          <li>Reduced resale value—buyers notice faded trim immediately</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Even brand new cars develop faded trim within 1-2 years in South Florida without protection. Regular restoration maintains that showroom appearance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Our Trim Restoration Process</h2>
        <ProcessSteps steps={[
          { title: "Deep Cleaning", description: "We clean all trim pieces with an all-purpose cleaner to remove dirt, old dressings, and contaminants that prevent product absorption." },
          { title: "Surface Preparation", description: "Heavily oxidized trim gets light abrasion to open the plastic pores and allow restoration product to penetrate deeply." },
          { title: "Restoration Application", description: "We apply Chemical Guys VRP or dedicated trim restorer, working it into the plastic with an applicator pad." },
          { title: "Absorption Time", description: "We allow the product to soak into the plastic. This is what separates restoration from temporary dressings—the color comes from within." },
          { title: "Buff and Protect", description: "We buff away excess product and apply a UV-protective coating to extend the restoration and prevent future fading." }
        ]} />
      </section>
    </div>

    <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
      <div class="sticky top-24 space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-[#1e3a5f] mb-4">Trim Restoration Quick Facts</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-[#c9a227] font-bold">$</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$50-$100 per vehicle</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-[#c9a227] mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-gray-600">30-60 minutes</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-[#c9a227] mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-gray-600">Restores black color</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-[#c9a227] mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-gray-600">UV protection included</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-[#c9a227] mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-gray-600">Lasts 3-6 months</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[#1e3a5f] rounded-xl p-6 text-white">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-4">Book Trim Restoration</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">
            Same-day appointments available throughout Fort Lauderdale.
          </p>
          <a href="tel:+17542152272" class="btn-accent w-full flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 5a2 2 0 012-2h3.28a1 1 0 01.948.684l1.498 4.493a1 1 0 01-.502 1.21l-2.257 1.13a11.042 11.042 0 005.516 5.516l1.13-2.257a1 1 0 011.21-.502l4.493 1.498a1 1 0 01.684.949V19a2 2 0 01-2 2h-1C9.716 21 3 14.284 3 6V5z" />
            </svg>
            754-215-2272
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-[#1e3a5f] mb-4">Related Services</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><a href={`${base}tire-dressing-fort-lauderdale/`} class="text-gray-600 hover:text-[#c9a227]">Tire Dressing</a></li>
            <li><a href={`${base}chrome-polishing-fort-lauderdale/`} class="text-gray-600 hover:text-[#c9a227]">Chrome Polishing</a></li>
            <li><a href={`${base}interior-protection-fort-lauderdale/`} class="text-gray-600 hover:text-[#c9a227]">Interior Protection</a></li>
            <li><a href={`${base}full-detail-fort-lauderdale/`} class="text-gray-600 hover:text-[#c9a227]">Full Detail</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</ServiceLayout>
